IRS990.Desc: FULFILLED REQUIREMENTS OF TITLE X GRANT TO INSURE:1. SUB-GRANTEES PROVIDED FAMILY PLANNING SERVICES AND OUTREACH SERVICES TO CREATE HEALTHY INDIVIDUALS, FAMILIES AND COMMUNITIES TO CLIENTS IN THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA. SERVED OVER 1,058,000 CLIENTS AT 340 CLINICAL SITES THROUGHOUT CA IN 2015.2. MAINTAINED WEBSITES FOR (A) TEENSOURCE, AND (B) TALK WITH YOUR KIDS.3. OVERSAW HIV INTEGRATION PROJECT.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: IPP:PROVIDED TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, TRAINING AND FUNDING TO DIVERSE CLINICS IN CA RELATED TO THE PREVENTION OF SEXUAL TRANSMITTED DISEASES (STDS) AND HIV IN AREAS WITH HIGH STD/HIV MORBIDITY. PROGRAM REACHED TARGET POPULATIONS THROUGH DIRECT PARTNER SERVICES AND USE OF DIGITAL PLATFORMS TO CONNECT USERS WITH SERVICES AND HEALTH INFORMATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COUNCIL RECOGNIZES THE IMPACT OF TAX POSITIONS ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD ("FASB") ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION ("ASC") TOPIC NO. 740, "ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES" ("ASC 740"). ASC 740 CLARIFIES THE UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES RECOGNIZED IN AN ENTERPRISE'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH FASB STATEMENT NO. 109, "ACCOUNTING FOR INCOME TAXES, AND PRESCRIBES A RECOGNITION AND MEASUREMENT OF A TAX POSITION TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN A TAX RETURN. ASC 740 ALSO PROVIDES GUIDANCE ON DE-RECOGNITION OF TAX BENEFITS, CLASSIFICATION ON THE BALANCE SHEET, INTEREST AND PENALTIES, DISCLOSURE AND TRANSITION. DURING THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31,2015, THE COUNCIL PERFORMED AN EVALUATION OF UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND DID NOT NOTE ANY MATTERS THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OR WHICH MAY HAVE AN EFFECT ON ITS TAX-EXEMPT STATUS.
PART XI LINE 2D: PUBLICATION REVENUE SHOWN NET OF COGS ON FORM 990. PART XII LINE 2D: PUBLICATION COSTS PRESENTED IN FUNCTIONAL EXPENSES ON FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD WILL HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY TO REVIEW THE RETURN BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED. ONCE THE RETURN IS APPROVED, THE RETURN WILL BE FILED ELECTRONICALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WITH THE BOARD AT LEAST ANNUALLY AND OBTAINS THEIR ACKNOWLEDGMENT IN WRITING BY SIGNING THE POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: JULIE RABINOVITZ'S COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE COMPRISED OF THE CHAIRS FROM EACH BOARD COMMITTEE AND THE AT-LARGE DIRECTOR. THE COMPENSATION TERMS ARE FOR AN ADDITIONAL THREE YEARS AS OUTLINED IN AN EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT. THE REVIEW WAS CONDUCTED IN LATE 2014 FOR THE YEARS 2016 TO 2018.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CALIFORNIA FAMILY HEALTH COUNCIL MAKES ITS FORMS 1023 AND 990 RETURNS AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST. THE INFORMATIONAL RETURNS ARE ALSO MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC THROUGH WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG, A PUBLIC WEBSITE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CALIFORNIA FAMILY HEALTH COUNCIL MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
